ays, and that the Party bureaucracy persistently denied the extreme right within the party assistance, access to funds, and representation within party organisations. It reaches a climax with the formulation of ‘plan’ threatening its own candidate if he failed to remove the extreme right from the Conservative Monday Club.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aRight and left (Political science)zGreat Britain. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aConservative Monday Club.  aConservative Party.  aaccess to funds.  abureaucracy.  aextreme right.  anegative attitude.  aparty assistance.  aparty organisations.  aprogressive groups.  arepresentation.1 aPitchford, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779412340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847794123423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847794123/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles